Chapter 5 — Activity Leakage

Why Good Deals Still Get Lost

Sales teams don't usually lose deals because they aren't working.

They lose deals because critical activities don't happen at the right time.

A follow-up gets delayed.

A meeting note never reaches the CRM.

A task is forgotten.

A customer email goes unanswered.

Individually, these feel like small operational misses.

Collectively, they create one of the biggest sources of revenue leakage.

This is Activity Leakage.

What is Activity Leakage?

Activity Leakage occurs when sales execution becomes inconsistent.

The opportunity still exists.

The customer may still be interested.

But the activities required to move the deal forward either never happen or are never recorded.

