Real-World Example

Two account executives each manage 30 opportunities.

Both report similar pipeline values.

The difference?

Rep A

Updates CRM after every interaction
Schedules the next step before ending a meeting
Never lets a follow-up become overdue

Rep B

Keeps notes in a notebook
Relies on memory
Updates CRM at the end of the week

On paper, both pipelines look similar.

In reality, only one pipeline reflects what's actually happening.

That's the cost of activity leakage.

Revenue Systems Insight

Sales success isn't just about doing more activities.

It's about making sure the right activities happen consistently—and are visible to everyone who depends on them.
